The paper discusses clustering categorical data, which is a common problem in data mining and falls under the scope of several CS sub-categories. 

- cs.DB (most likely) - This sub-category deals with database systems and data management, which includes clustering algorithms. 
- cs.LG - This sub-category covers machine learning, which includes clustering algorithms as a subfield. 
- cs.IR - This sub-category deals with information retrieval, which involves clustering techniques for text and other types of data. 
- cs.DS - This sub-category covers data structures and algorithms, which includes clustering algorithms. 
- cs.AI - This sub-category covers artificial intelligence, which includes clustering algorithms as a subfield.
